<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F913F3E6-E328-4D4A-BB0B-D7722E5A6786" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Aphyolebias Costa 1998:78" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aphyolebias</taxonomicName>
comprises seven species, all endemic to the Amazonian basin (Costa, 2003c): 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peruensis">A. peruensis (Myers)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wischmanni">A. wischmanni (Seegers)</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C59A445D-9607-4D11-A70A-640D32816D0B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Aphyolebias schleseri Costa 2003:160" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schleseri">A. schleseri Costa</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Marañón-Ucayali-Amazonas">Maranon-Ucayali-Amazonas</normalizedToken>
river system, western Amazon, Peru, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubrocaudatus">A. rubrocaudatus (Seegers)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obliquus">A. obliquus (Costa, Sarmiento &amp; Barrera)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D8CC4AFE-288B-43F5-AB19-A09C002FE712" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Aphyolebias claudiae Costa 2003:158" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="claudiae">A. claudiae Costa</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B75B546B-4BFC-455C-B539-5EFD071EDA7D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Aphyolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Aphyolebias manuensis Costa 2003:161" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="manuensis">A. manuensis (Costa)</taxonomicName>
from the Madre de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dios-Beni-Mamoré-Madeira">Dios-Beni-Mamore-Madeira</normalizedToken>
river system in Peru and Bolivia, southern Amazon.
</paragraph>
